Package us.daveread.edu.graphics.test

Enum FractalColorScheme

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<FractalColorScheme>
      • us.daveread.edu.graphics.test.FractalColorScheme
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<FractalColorScheme>
    public enum FractalColorScheme
extends java.lang.Enum<FractalColorScheme>
    Color schemes for rendering fractal plots. The coloring is done using three groups of colors. Each pair is used to interpolate a range of colors for a "zone" of the fractal. The three groups (zones) represent the outside (clearly not a member of the set), border (close to being a member), and member (many iterations before diverging).
